. In contrast to these, she places the writings of Zora Neale Hurston, Maxine Hong Kingston, Gloria Anzaldúa, and Leslie Marmon Silko, whose works model a cultural literacy that weaves connections across many local knowledges and many ways of knowing.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCulture. 0aEducational anthropologyzUnited States. 0aLiteracyzUnited States. 0aMulticultural educationzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/72521840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292798250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292798250/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK